[normal]To this end, the presentation of Dr. A. Neil Hutton gives you the views of an outstanding and independent scientist that cannot be disregarded. He is not alone but a member of a very large community of sc[bold]ientists, which are not linked to IPCC.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]SUMMARY
[normal]The IPCC expect us to accept that with hundreds of climate models which do not match observations and measurements, they are 95% confident that warming since 1951 is human caused.  The global average surfac[bold]e record only shows warming in concert with increased CO2 between 1978 -1997.  That is only 19 of the past 63 years amounting to only 30%.  There is therefore a 70% chance that CO2 and atmospheric warming are not correlated and the claim that warming is hu[bold]man caused [bold]can not[bold] be supported[bold]Model studies do not match the observed climate variability because of the limitation of their assumptions and can be shown to be 97.5% wrong.[bold]In order to characterize modern warming as unprecedented the IPCC simply evade th[bold]e eight Holocene warming and cooling cycles of which our modern warming is the last and coolest.  Evidence is incontrovertible that the Roman Warm Period and the Medieval Warm Period had [bold]world wide[bold] effect and were at least 1degree C warmer[bold]IPPC simply igno[bold]re the evidence from the early history of the earth. Claim that CO2 content is at its most elevated in the last 200,000 years when in fact it is at its lowest levels in geological history.  The very high atmospheric CO2 content in the early history of the [bold]planet [bold]can not[bold] be reconciled with IPCC forecasts and projections.  According to IPPC forecasts the land and oceans would not be habitable at established ranges of atmospheric CO2 documented to be anywhere from 16 to 100 times current levels during the [bold]Prot[bold]erozoic[bold] and Palaeozoic (0.25 – 3.5 Billion years ago).   Thus CO2 [bold]can not[bold] be a significant driver of climate.[bold]IPCC in an effort,  to preserve credibility have simply written off the Sun the major source of our planetary energy    Because solar output is re[bold]latively [bold]constant, IPCC have chosen to ignore a large body of evidence linking solar variability with climate which has the support of abundant peer reviewed measurement observation and experiment to corroborate the Sun, together with Cosmic influences,  a[bold]re the main driver of climate. [bold] The IPCC is a deeply flawed process not scientific but political.  From the perspective of jurisprudence CO2 is on trial for warming the planet, and a massive prosecution has been mounted with popular support, but no defenc[bold]e.  Any criticism was regarded as heretical and although no one has been burned at the stake many careers and funding have gone up in flames.   There has been a serious loss of objectivity and integrity in this process.  How can the Summary for Policymaker[bold]s precede the Scientific reports in order to have consistency?   As the evidence for warming by CO2 has been discredited the IPCC have simply become more adamant in their claims.[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]COMMENT ON AR5[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]1)[bold] 
[normal]The IPCC wish us to believe that hundreds of climate model runs which do not match observations are still proof of warming.  In normal scientific protocols, in use since the 17th Century, if the hypothesis is not corroborated by observation and measurement
[normal], it is 
[normal]WRONG[bold].  In the latest IPCC Assessment, (AR5) the Summary for Policymakers claims 95% certainty that the warming since 1951 is human caused while having presented no evidence to support such a link
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2)[bold].[bold]  An inspection of the actual record shows tha
[normal]t the global average temperature actually cooled between 1951 and 1978, so much so, that a number of scientists wrote to President Nixon warning of a coming Ice Age.  A reasonable assumption given that we live in an interglacial warm period.  Th
[normal]ese warm pe
[normal]riods are episodic (
[normal]approximately 15-20,000 years
[normal] long,
[normal] while gla
[normal]cial episodes last from 80 - 11
[normal]0,000
[normal] years
[normal].  There have been 5 cycles in the last 450,000 years
[normal]. (see Petit et al 1999) 
[normal] and in AR5 Working Group I it is stated, 
[normal]There is [bold]high confidence [bold]that[bold] changes in atmospheric CO2 concentration play an important role in[bold] [bold]glacial-interglacial cycles[bold].   
[normal]This
[normal] assertion
[normal] is a total contradiction of the peer reviewed literature which shows
[normal] that CO2 is not involved in the warming process but follows as a result of degassing of melting ice.
[normal]  Lags of 800 t0 1300 years have been reported by authors such as ( Fischer et al 1999, 
[normal]Monnin
[normal] et al 2001, 
[normal]Mudelsee
[normal] 2001 and 
[normal]Caillon
[normal] 2003)
[normal] 
[normal] There is no mec
[normal]hanism to produce the CO2 
[normal] in this strongly cyclical system
[normal] and, more critically, how does it disappear with the onset of a new cooling trend?  
[normal]It is quite clear that CO2 is a passive player in glacial interglacial cycles[bold], and[bold] its manifestation[bold] is[bold] an indic[bold]ation[bold] only[bold] of its solubility, high in cold conditions and low in warm conditions.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]3).[bold] 
[normal]Between1978 and 1997 the climate warmed correlative with rising 
[normal]atmospheric CO2 but ceased in 1997 and has remained stable since.  Therefore warming occurred in only 19 
[normal]of 63 years which is only 30%.
[normal], 
[normal](
[normal]an unlikely 
[normal]p
[normal]robability, in IPCC terminology)
[normal]  
[normal]There is therefore a 70% chance[bold], (likely probability[bold] in IPCC terminology[bold])[bold] that CO2 and warming are not correlated.[bold]  
[normal]T[bold]he IPCC claim of[bold] 95% confidence that warming since 1951 is human caused[bold] is[bold] not be [bold]supported[bold] by the evidence[bold].[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]4).[bold] 
[normal]The fact is that climate models have been unable to match observed climate variability because of the limitations of their assumptions, in particular, the 
[normal]supposedly dominant role of CO2.  It is well recognized by climatologists that CO2 without amplification or positive feedbacks 
[normal]can not
[normal] warm the at
[normal]mosphere in the manner proposed by IPCC scientists. 
[normal]  The failure of models to match actual observations
[normal] is a 
[normal]clear indication that the model assu
[normal]mptions are wrong, and not that the heat is mysteriously hiding we know not where!
[normal]  Furthermore
[normal],
[normal] a model is only a hypothesis awaiting corroboration by measurement and observation
[normal].  As demonstrated[bold] in Fig.1[bold] below measure[bold]ments and observations show that the IPPC models are 97.5% wrong [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Fig 1 After Spencer 2013, (
[normal]http://www.drroyspencer.com/page/2/
[normal])  The figure documents that 97.5% of the models warm faster than the observations of the surface (green) and the troposphere (blue).  This demonstrates that there is no basis to claim 95% probability
[normal] that warming is human caused.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5[bold]).[bold]  It is commonplace to read that  atmospheric CO2 content is at its most elevated in the last 200,000 years, but it is usual to avoid the ‘inconvenient truth” that CO2 is at the lowest levels in the last 500million years and is  at minimum levels for a hea
[normal]lthy biosphere.  A new detailed report (
[normal]Idso
[normal] 2013) details the benefits to the planet of elevated CO2 
[normal]'The results indicate that the annual total monetary value of this benefit grew from about $20 billion in 1961 to over $160 billion by 2011, amounting to [bold]a total sum of $3.5 trillion over the 50-year period 1961-2011.[bold]&#xa0;[bold] Projecting the monetary value of this positive externality forward in time reveals it will likely bestow an additional $11.6 trillion on crop production between now and 2050'[bold] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6[bold]).[bold] 
[normal]In the las
[normal]t 15,000 years, within the current interglacial, the climate has had eight episodes of warming and cooling, in recurrent cycles, all in general comparable to our modern warming period, but clearly lacking any influence by CO2.  The only feature that distin
[normal]guishes the modern warming from eight previous cycles is that it is cooler. 
[normal]( 
[normal]see
[normal] Huang et al, 2000: Jiang et al 2007: Clegg et al 2010
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]: Dietrich 2007
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]: 
[normal]Fillipi
[normal] et al 1999 and Yang et al 2009). 
[normal]Furthermore there are literally hundreds of peer 
[normal]reviewed art
[normal]icles describing the Medieval Warm Period and the Little Ice Ages’ global occurrence (
[normal]www.co2science.org
[normal]) but in AR5, WGI, p.5-5 it 
[normal]states
[normal], 
[normal]“[bold]With [bold]high confidence[bold], these intervals were not as synchronous across seas[bold]ons and regions as the warming since the mid-20th century[bold]”[bold].  [bold] This is a deliberate evasion not supported by published literature, and is present only to avoid acknowledging that many climate cycles occurred in the Holocene[bold] from solar forcing,[bold] totally indep[bold]endent of CO2[bold], while our current warming is neither unique,[bold] unusual or occurring at exceptional rates[bold] [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]7[bold])[bold].
[normal] 
[normal]There is abundant observational evidence, in published literature, to show that the two prior warm periods, the Roman Warm Period and the Medieval 
[normal]Warm Period, were as much as 1 º C warmer than our late 20
[normal]th
[normal] Century warming.  Since the modern warming initiates in the Little Ice Age as solar activity recovers from a 70 year hiatus in Sun spot activity then the warming into the 20
[normal]th
[normal] Century is certainl
[normal]y the result of increased solar activity.  There is no signal to indicate the point at which natural warming is supplemented by the effect of CO2.  Nor is there any signature which can identify anthropogenic versus natural warming.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8[bold]).[bold] 
[normal]The focus by the IP
[normal]CC on only the last 50 years of Climate variability is like trying to describe a large richly furnished drawing room through the keyhole.  What is most important is not what is in the AR5 rep
[normal]ort but what has been left 
[normal]out, or glibly avoided
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]m
[normal]ost important
[normal]ly, the
[normal] history of the evolution of the Earth’s atmosphere, 5.4 billion years
[normal] of geological history
[normal], which
[normal] utterly con
[normal]tradicts a major role for CO2 as a climate driver
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9[bold]).[bold] In the beginning the Earth’
[normal]s atmosphere was anoxic
[normal] 
[normal]and contained high volumes of 
[normal]Nitrogen, CO2
[normal], water vapour
[normal] as well as molecules that are true pollutants like Sulphur Dioxide (SO2), Hydrogen Sulphide (H2S), Methane (CH2), 
[normal]and Nitrogen Oxides (NOX)
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal] Then how did 
[normal]this essentially 
[normal]toxic
[normal] atmosphere come to support life and supply oxygen.
[normal]  Why! 
[normal] 
[normal]b
[normal]ecause of CO2 along
[normal] with the evolution of prokaryotic bacteria
[normal].  In the early oceans 3.5 Billion years ago very primitive life forms, 
[normal]cyanobacteria
[normal], which were aquatic and photosynthetic, gradually became very abundant.  Photosynthesis allowed the
[normal] organisms to utilise sunlight to digest CO2 converting it to cellulose and sugar molecules while releasing Oxygen (O2
[normal]), the
[normal] 
[normal]breath of life for the Animal Kingdom.  These organisms occurred in such massive quantities that they oxygenated the atmosphere to 
[normal]current oxygen levels.  Therefore, without CO2 and bacteria there would be no life on the planet.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]10[bold])[bold].
[normal] Photosynthesis
[normal] initiates a process of fixing and sequestering carbon
[normal] which continues
[normal] throughout geological history
[normal].  B
[normal]y the close of the 
[normal]Proterozoic
[normal] ex
[normal]tensive carbonate platforms and 
[normal]stromatolitic
[normal] reefs are commonplace and have fixed thousands of 
[normal]gigatons
[normal] of carbon.  
[normal] Studies indicate that at 1.4Biillion years the 
[normal]Proterozoic
[normal] atmosphere contained
[normal] 10 to 200 times current levels of CO2.
